714952f-a.text:
140 West 102nd Street, south side between Amsterdam and Columbus Avenue and 101st Street to 102nd
Street, showing P.S. 179.
Board of Education, N.Y.C.
1920

715969f-a.text:
869 Amsterdam Ave., east side, between West 102nd and 103rd Streets, showing a 2 story structure that lies in the line of a road, which forked eastward from the old Bloomingdale Road (now Broadway). At the rear of this building lot it turned northeastward for several blocks to again run eastward on the present line of West 105th Street. One, Marie Schmidt, is given by the photographer as the owner.
About 1924.
W. B. Vernam.

714953f-a.text:
West 102nd Street, west from No. 178-180 (left, building with flag) a point east of Amsterdam Ave., across same to the North (Hudson) River, showing the south curb under repair. No. 178-80 is Station H, United States Post Office and adjoins P.S. No. 179 (partially shown).
September 8, 1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
